CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 18, 1954, pg. 14 reads: "B'Nai B'Rith Art Contest - Awards to senior high school entrants in B'Nai B'rith Women's Council's eighth annual art contest were awarded Monday at the Board of Education Building on Bellefield Avenue. Shown on the left, with their $10 senior prize are Donald Moss, Allderdice High School; Ora Jantarof, Allderdice High School, and Constance Turner, Westinghouse High School.  Winners of $5 junior prizes are shown on the right.  They are, left to right: Franes Valko, Allderdice High; Barbara Abelson, Allderdice High, and Ruth Grossman, Allderdice High. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Woman wearing dark pleated skirt, handing check to boy wearing dark suit, and two young women, one holding two pieces of artwork, posed in Board of Education Building for B'nai B'rith Women's Council art contest, Oakland
